sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant App as Jain Menu App<br/>(PWA)
    participant Weather as Weather API<br/>(OpenWeatherMap)
    participant Claude as Claude API<br/>(Haiku — scoring)
    participant YT as YouTube Data API<br/>(v3)
    participant Cook as Cook<br/>(WhatsApp share)

    User->>App: opens app (home page)

    par Fetch context in parallel
        App->>Weather: GET /weather?city=Mumbai
        Weather-->>App: 38°C, humid, sunny
    and
        App->>App: read user history<br/>(localStorage — last 30 days)
        Note over App: novelty: what hasn't been made recently<br/>recency: last time this appeared
    end

    App->>Claude: score all Jain recipes
    Note over Claude: Input: recipe list + weather + history<br/>Score each on:<br/>• weather fit (hot/cold/seasonal)<br/>• novelty (days since last made)<br/>• ingredient price (seasonal index)
    Claude-->>App: ranked recipes with scores

    App->>YT: search Jain cooking videos<br/>(top recipe titles, filter: shorts + recent)
    YT-->>App: candidate videos

    App->>Claude: score videos
    Note over Claude: Score each on:<br/>• novelty (not shown in last 14 days)<br/>• recency (upload date)<br/>• weather match (title/desc relevance)
    Claude-->>App: top 3 videos ranked

    App->>User: home page renders
    Note over User,App: Card 1: Recipe A<br/>☀️ Weather fit: 9/10 🌟 Novelty: 8/10 💰 Price: 7/10<br/>+ YT short thumbnail<br/><br/>Card 2: Recipe B (scores shown)<br/>Card 3: Recipe C (scores shown)

    User->>App: selects a card (recipe + video)
    App->>User: full recipe detail<br/>ingredients + method + YT embed

    User->>App: taps "Share with Cook"
    App->>App: compile cook note<br/>(recipe name + ingredient list + portions)
    App->>Cook: WhatsApp share<br/>"Today: Stuffed Capsicum (Jain). Ingredients: ..."
    Cook-->>User: 👍
